The wait is almost over — the Stranger Things 5 Final Season is here. As Hawkins faces its darkest hour, Eleven and her friends must confront Vecna one last time in a battle that will decide the fate of their world. Starring Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, Sadie Sink, David Harbour, Winona Ryder, and Jamie Campbell Bower, this is the end of an era. Watch the Final Season Trailer 2 for Stranger Things 5, only on Netflix.

The inspiration behind this video:
The wait is over. The Stranger Things 5 Final Season Trailer 2 has arrived, bringing the epic conclusion to Netflix’s most beloved saga. Starring Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, Noah Schnapp, Caleb McLaughlin, and Sadie Sink, this Stranger Things 5 Official Teaser reveals new dangers, new dimensions, and the ultimate showdown between Eleven and Vecna. Join David Harbour as Chief Hopper, Winona Ryder as Joyce Byers, and the full cast including Gaten Matarazzo, Maya Hawke, Joe Keery, Natalia Dyer, Charlie Heaton, and Cara Buono as they face the end of Hawkins’ story. With Jonathan Byers, Will Byers, Nancy Wheeler, Robin Buckley, Steve Harrington, Mike Wheeler, Lucas, Max, and Holly Wheeler, every character’s fate will finally be decided in stranger things season 5 trailer,stranger things.

Experience the power, the mystery, and the heart of Stranger Things Season 5 — only on Netflix. This is where it all ends. Prepare yourself for the darkest chapter yet in the Stranger Things 5 Final Season. Presented by Rotten Tomatoes TV, FilmSpot Trailer, MovieGasm, KinoCheck, EmergencyAwesome, and IGN TV Trailer, this Netflix trailer offer a first look at the spine-chilling events awaiting in STRANGER THINGS 5. snippet.title: Creedence Clearwater Revival - Have You Ever Seen The Rain (Fan Celebration Version)
snippet.description:
We are celebrating your comments for the official Have You Ever Seen The Rain music video. Thank you for supporting CCR! 

About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.

Encore

snippet.title: Transport Fever 3 - Vehicle Trailer
snippet.description:
We’re excited to reveal the very first in-game trailer for Transport Fever 3, featuring some of its most stunning vehicles!

Transport Fever 3 features the largest fleet in the series, ranging from historical classics to the most sophisticated high-tech methods for travel. Vehicles are the stars of the show and this video gives you a look at some of the upgraded favourites and brand new options running in-game for the first time.

We've got ships, helicopters, buses, trams, trucks and, of course, trains for you to feast your eyes upon, and if you look just a little more closely you'll see a couple of features we haven't shown yet.

Transport Fever 3 is releasing in 2026!

snippet.title: Il y a quelqu’un d’étrange derrière ma porte... (No I’m Not a Human)
snippet.description:
Salut ! Aujourd'hui on se retrouve pour parler d'un jeu que vous connaissez certainement déjà: No I'm Not a Human !
Comme l'indique la durée de la vidéo effectivement j'ai beaucoup parlé mais promis c'est intéressant ! (enfin ça dépend des gens en vrai c'est vrai que de parler pendant une heure et quatorze minutes d'un jeu indé c'est pas normal pour certains fin bref vous captez l'idée)

Illustrations/Animation: Dessinées par Moi
Montage: Moi
Script: moi ouais bah en gros j'ai tout fait quoi

Ma vidéo sur la démo:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jx-zJpua2U8

Sources:
Le jeu
https://no-i-am-not-a-human.fandom.com/wiki/No,_I%27m_not_a_Human_Wiki
https://www.youtube.com/@AlexxKister
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/No,_I%27m_Not_a_Human
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_Meridian
https://www.deviantart.com/john-d-salvatore/art/The-Judge-743222384
https://misterwalsh.tumblr.com/post/113829643080/judge-holden-from-blood-meridian-or-the-evening?

(Concernant les théories sur le jeu, vu que y en a énormément et que j'ai repris des bouts par ci par là sur reddit/des forums, je peux pas créditer les auteurs, je pense qu'ils sont même impossible à retrouver vu comment ça se propage ces trucs là mais si vous penser savoir d'où viennent certaines des théories en questions n'hésitez pas à me le dire)

(Aussi je suis désolé si j'ai pas parlé de quelques uns des messages du jeu, c'était soit par manque de temps ou parce que ça me paraissait évident mais certains auront remarqué qu'il y a d'autres trucs à dire dans le sous-texte)

Dites moi si j'ai oublié quelque choses !

1:59 Ma première run
34:34 Duel contre le justicier
37:04 Ma première run (bis)

snippet.title: Caelis - Too Late to Say Love ( Official Music Video )
snippet.description:
💔 Too Late to Say Love ( Official Music Video ) tells the story of a guitarist who once fell for his neighbor - a fleeting chance at love that he kept hidden, waiting for the “right time.” But when she reached out, he was away chasing small stages, and by the next day she was gone without a trace. Years later, success finally came, and on a distant stage fate brought them face to face again. She revealed the truth: she had waited for him that night, hoping to hear the words he never said. In that moment, he felt both the sting of regret and the quiet relief of finally knowing why she left.

🎶 This is a Melancholic Cinematic Reggae Ballad in A minor, blending nylon guitar arpeggios, heartbeat-like percussion, and swelling strings with a warm, mournful baritone voice. The hook “Too late to say love” echoes like a confession whispered to the night.

✨ Let this song carry you into the ache of missed moments, the silence of unspoken words, and the haunting truth that some chances never return.

Too Late to Say Love ( Video Lyrics ) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zQqTcMfGupE

#caelis
